  title       = {Generative {AI} for Infrastructure as Code ({IaC}): Automating {DevOps} Configuration, Scripting, and Workflow Management with {LLMs}},
  year        = {2024},
  month       = {september},
  day         = {22},
  abstract    = {This paper examines the application of generative {AI} in Infrastructure as Code ({IaC}), focusing on automating {DevOps} configuration, scripting, and workflow management using large language models ({LLMs}). As organizations embrace {IaC} to streamline infrastructure management, the complexity of configuration scripts often poses challenges. Generative {AI} can simplify and enhance these processes by automatically generating code snippets, optimizing configurations, and managing workflows. This study outlines the framework for integrating generative {AI} into {IaC} practices, highlighting its potential to improve efficiency, reduce errors, and accelerate deployment cycles. The findings suggest that leveraging {LLMs} in {IaC} significantly enhances productivity and fosters more resilient infrastructure management.},
